<item>
            <title>[LU-11203] Create release packages for lustre</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11203</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Similar to how EPEL and ZFS have release packages, which move the repo files into place, it would be useful for Lustre to have a release package.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Prior art: &lt;a href=&quot;https://gist.github.com/jgrund/7fd8d8aa849a0ef57e11a980d8427dd2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://gist.github.com/jgrund/7fd8d8aa849a0ef57e11a980d8427dd2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It could be installed like:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;yum install &lt;a href=&quot;https://downloads.whamcloud.com/public/lustre/lustre-X/elX/lustre-release.rpm&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://downloads.whamcloud.com/public/lustre/lustre-X/elX/lustre-release.rpm&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Open question:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Does it make sense to have multiple release rpms for server / client / mlnx?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
